== 5. Strategic Recommendations ==

=== 5.1 Positioning Strategy ===

{{warning}}
**Don't position as "another fact-checker"—position as:**

* "Fact-checking infrastructure"
* "Evidence Model platform"
* "Transparency layer for claims"
{{/warning}}

=== 5.2 Partnership Opportunities ===

|=Partner Type|=Value Proposition|=Examples
|**Monitoring Leaders**|FactHarbor as verdict backend for their monitoring|Full Fact AI, Factiverse
|**Ecosystem Integration**|Structured ClaimReview producer for search/social|Google, Meta, IFCN
|**Academic/Research**|Real-world testbed for debate protocols|ED2D authors, ETH Zurich (Ash)
|**Newsroom Workflows**|Deep-reasoning tool for investigative journalism|BBC Verify, NRK

=== 5.3 Competitive Moats to Build ===

1. **Multi-Source Evidence Resilience:** Close the C13 gap by adding Semantic Scholar and Google Fact Check API.
1. **Calibration Leadership:** Establish C18/C13 as the industry standard for automated fact-checking transparency.
1. **Debate-Triggered Re-search:** Implement the ED2D pattern to become the first production system with dynamic retrieval.

=== 5.4 Market Timing Advantages ===

* Meta exit creates demand for independent tools
* Google removal of ClaimReview rich results → need for new infrastructure
* Big Tech funding cuts for fact-checkers (Full Fact crisis) → need for efficient automation
* AI Act (Aug 2025) → demand for auditable, calibrated fact-checking

